-- Gold Gains After U.S. Adds Fewer Jobs Than Forecast in March
-- B y   M i l l i e   M u n s h i
-- 2012-04-06T12:34:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-06/gold-gains-after-u-s-adds-fewer-jobs-than-forecast-in-march.html
Gold in  London  rose for a second
straight day after U.S. employers added fewer than jobs than
forecast.  Bullion for immediate delivery gained 0.6 percent to
$1,640.63 an ounce at 8:33 a.m.  New York  time. Trading on the
Comex in New York is closed today for Good Friday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Millie Munshi at 
